text.tspan: The module is a frequency divider for clock,
trigger or gate signals, designed to be a source of
lower frequencies, particularly for rhythm uses.
The clock input (CLK) will take any signal +/-10V.
At the outputs, you have access to four different
sub-divided clock signals, from half the clock
levels of the output signals are 0V and about +5V.
The module also has a reset (RST) input.
